com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec

Interface DataDictionary


  • public interface DataDictionary
    A class that houses all known fields loaded from an RDM field dictionary and their corresponding enum types loaded from an enum type dictionary. The dictionary also saves general information about the dictionary itself - this is found in the "!tag" comments of the file or in the summary data of dictionaries encoded via the official domain model. The data dictionary must be loaded prior to using the methods to access dictionary entries.
    See Also:
    DictionaryEntry, EnumType, MfFieldTypes

      • extractDictionaryType

        int extractDictionaryType(DecodeIterator iter,
                          Int dictionaryType,
                          Error error)
        Extract dictionary type from the encoded payload of a UPA message where the domain type is DICTIONARY. Typical use:
        1. Call Msg.decode().
        2. If domainType is DICTIONARY, call this method.
        3. Call appropriate dictionary decode method based on returned dictionary type (e.g., if returned type is FIELD_DEFINITIONS, call decodeFieldDictionary()).
        Parameters:
        iter - An iterator to use. Must be set to the encoded payload of the dictionary message.
        dictionaryType - The dictionary type, from DictionaryTypes.
        error - UPA Error, to be populated in event of an error.
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes. If success, dictionary type is populated. If failure, dictionary type not available.
        See Also:
        DecodeIterator, Dictionary.Types

      • encodeFieldDictionary

        int encodeFieldDictionary(EncodeIterator iter,
                          Int currentFid,
                          int verbosity,
                          Error error)
        Encode the field definitions dictionary information into a data payload according the domain model, using the field information from the entries present in this dictionary. This method supports building the encoded data in multiple parts -- if there is not enough available buffer space to encode the entire dictionary, subsequent calls can be made to this method, each producing the next segment of fields.
        Parameters:
        iter - Iterator to be used for encoding. Prior to each call, the iterator must be cleared and initialized to the buffer to be used for encoding.
        currentFid - Tracks which fields have been encoded in case of multi-part encoding. Must be initialized to dictionary->minFid on the first call and is updated with each successfully encoded part.
        verbosity - The desired verbosity to encode.
        error - UPA error, to be populated in event of an error.
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes, CodecReturnCodes.DICT_PART_ENCODED when encoding parts is success CodecReturnCodes.SUCCESS for final part or single complete payload.
        See Also:
        EncodeIterator, Dictionary.VerbosityValues

      • decodeFieldDictionary

        int decodeFieldDictionary(DecodeIterator iter,
                          int verbosity,
                          Error error)
        Decode the field dictionary information contained in a data payload according to the domain model. This method may be called multiple times on the same dictionary, to load information from dictionaries that have been encoded in multiple parts.
        Parameters:
        iter - An iterator to use. Must be set to the encoded buffer.
        verbosity - The desired verbosity to decode. See Dictionary.VerbosityValues.
        error - UPA error, to be populated in event of an error.
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes
        See Also:
        DecodeIterator, Dictionary.VerbosityValues

                             int verbosity,
                             Error error)
        Encode the enumerated types dictionary according the domain model, using the information from the tables and referencing fields present in this dictionary. Note: This method will use the type ASCII_STRING for the DISPLAY array.
        Parameters:

        verbosity - The desired verbosity to encode.
        error - UPA Error, to be populated in event of an error.
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes
        See Also:
